Deploy a Scalable Web Application: Deploy a simple web application (e.g., a blog, or to-do list app) using cloud infrastructure. Implement autoscaling and load-balancing features to demonstrate scalability. 

**Deploying a to-do app on Elastic AWS(Elastic Beanstalk)**

The web app deployed is a blog app developed using [Django,](https://www.djangoproject.com/) a Python web application Framework.  The app has basic features below:

- Users can create an account, log in, and log in.   
- Users can reset their passwords  
- Users can edit their profile  
- Users can create, edit, and view blog posts.

Tech stack:

# **AWS Elastic Beanstalk \- Platform As A Service**

​​AWS Elastic Beanstalk is AWS implementation for PaaS.  You can simply upload your application code, and the service automatically handles details such as resource provisioning, load balancing, auto-scaling, and monitoring. Elastic Beanstalk uses core AWS services such as Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2), Amazon Elastic Container Service (ECS), AWS Auto Scaling, and Elastic Load Balancing (ELB) to easily support applications that need to scale to serve millions of users.

**Environment Set up.**

EC2 Instances \-  2 Instances  
Load balancer \- Nginix, Auto Scaling enabled.
